     <div type="to_the_reader">
   <pb facs="4"/>
   <head>TO THE READER.</head>
   <opener>
      <salute>Christian READER,</salute>
   </opener>
   <p>
      <seg rend="decorInit">I</seg> Conceive how difficult an adventure it is, to put my poore Talent unto publike view, see<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ing greater graces kept in silence: But, I know how hard it is to hide, and therefore deeme it better to ha<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>zard it then my selfe.</p>
   <p>View then the matter which may pleasure thee, and favour the Au<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>thor with the furtherance of thy prayers; and the Author of every good gift, give thee faith and feare
<pb facs="5"/>here, and the end of both hereaf<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ter: In suite for which, I re<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>maine pressed ever ready unto any Christian Office.</p>
   <closer>
      <signed>Thine in all Chri<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>stian duty, E. A.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
